    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The RLP decoder is working as intended in this case. If an input list contains less than the reqired number of elements, the remaining struct fields are set to their zero value. [This is documented](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/22893b7ac925c49168c119f293ea8befc3aff5cc/rlp/decode.go#L44).\n\nThe eth protocol layer should reject messages if the content is not valid. Not valid includes \"has fields that are `nil` but shouldn't be\".\n",
